-- Czech Stocks: CEZ, Erste Group Bank, Vienna Insurance Group Move
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-05-29T14:51:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-29/czech-stocks-cez-erste-group-bank-vienna-insurance-group-move.html
The Czech Republic’s  PX (PX)  stock index
rose 1.4 percent to 878.1 at the close in Prague, rebounding
from a five-month low.  The following were among the most active  equities  in the
Czech market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  CEZ AS (CEZ)   rose 1.5 percent to 724.5 koruna, snapping
a two-day drop. Electricity for next-year delivery in Germany,
where the biggest Czech utility exports part of its output, rose
0.7 percent to 49.60 euros per megawatt-hour, poised for the
contract’s highest close in more than two weeks.  Erste Group Bank AG (RBAG)   of Austria added 2.8 percent
to 378 koruna, its second day of gains.  Vienna Insurance Group
AG (VIG)   climbed 2.2 percent to 738 koruna. European stocks
gained after U.S. data showed that the housing market in the
world’s largest economy is stabilizing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in  Prague  at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  